    "ARMY RESERVE Secretary of War Taft Has Sent Eleven Bills to Con gress to Increase Military Efficiency NEW FORGE TO BE ORGANIZED ___ ITS NUMBERS WOULD NOT EX CEED 60000 MEN WHO WOULD HAVE SERVED NOT LESS THAN ONE ENLISTMENT WASHINGTON Jan 31 1906Sec tary of War Taft has sent to Congress eleven bills prepared by the general staff yf the army for increasing the efficiency tike army Some of the measures are regarded as highly important They were prepared after a series of consulta tions with the head of the committee an military aha ir in both the Senate and the House One off the most important of the bills seat to Congress today is entitled A bill to reorganize and increase the effi ciency pf the artillery of the United States This measure provides for the reparation of the coast and field artillery ud for an increase in the coast artillery of 181 officers and 4923 enlisted men over the present authorized strengtr the bill provides also for the arganizo tion of the field artillery into six regi ments of six batteries each with an in crease over the present authorized num bers of 115 officers and 1310"
